CHAPTER 16
Research Objectives
Investigate whether a distributed electro-hydraulic architecture can:

Improve transient torque delivery.
Reduce peak stress on individual drivetrain components.
Improve thermal distribution.
Increase redundancy and fault tolerance.
Maintain acceptable efficiency despite added hydraulic complexity.
These objectives require quantitative simulation and experimental validation before performance claims can be made.

